  "prompt": "How do I reset my Gmail Password?",
  "response": "Resetting your Gmail password is a straightforward process. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n### **Step 1: Go to the Gmail Sign-in Page**\n1. Open your web browser and go to [https://mail.google.com](https://mail.google.com).\n2. Enter your Gmail email address and click **Next**.\n3. On the password entry page, click **Forgot password?**.\n\n### **Step 2: Verify Your Identity**\n1. Google will ask you to verify your identity. You can do this by:\n   - **Recovery email**: Google will send a verification code to your recovery email address.\n   - **Recovery phone number**: Google will send a code via text message or call your recovery phone number.\n   - **Answering security questions**: If you\u2019ve set up security questions, you\u2019ll need to answer them correctly.\n\n### **Step 3: Create a New Password**\n1. Once your identity is verified, you\u2019ll be prompted to create a new password.\n2. Enter your new password and confirm it by typing it again.\n3. Click **Change Password**.\n\n### **Step 4: Sign In with Your New Password**\n1. Go back to the Gmail sign-in page.\n2. Enter your email address and new password to log in.\n\n### **Tips for a Strong Password**\n- Use a mix of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols.\n- Avoid using easily guessable information like your name or birthdate.\n- Make it at least 8 characters long.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during the process, you can visit the [Google Account Recovery page](https://accounts.google.com/signin/recovery) for additional assistance.",
